com.siperian.sif.message.mrm

Class RemoveMatchedRecordsRequest

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.siperian.sif.message.SiperianRequest
      • com.siperian.sif.message.SiperianObjectRequest
        • com.siperian.sif.message.mrm.RemoveMatchedRecordsRequest
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    RecordKeyProvider, SiperianObjectUidProvider, Serializable

    public class RemoveMatchedRecordsRequest
extends SiperianObjectRequest
implements SiperianObjectUidProvider, RecordKeyProvider
    If user decides that one object is not a match with list of other objects, then this will remove corresponding records from [BO]_MTCH table. For example, if object A doesn't match with B and C, this request will remove following entries if they exist from [BO]_MTCH table.
    • A - B
    • B - A
    • A - C
    • C - A

    It will also remove the associated task from the task table.

    Required Parameters:
    • SiperianObjectUid - type and name of the base object or package to be used
    • RecordKey - record key which doesn't match with the list of record keys.
    • RecordKeyList - list of record keys.

    Usage Example: The following example flags 111 and 222 for automerge. 

    
 RemoveMatchedRecordsRequest request = new RemoveMatchedRecordsRequest();
 request.setSiperianObjectUid(SiperianObjectType.PACKAGE.makeUid("C_PARTY"));
 request.setRecordKey(RecordKey.sourceKey("A", "Acme"));
 ArrayList keys = new ArrayList();
 keys.add(RecordKey.sourceKey("B", "Acme"));
 keys.add(RecordKey.sourceKey("C", "Acme"));
 request.setRecordKeyList(keys);
 RemoveMatchedRecordsResponse response = sipClient.process(request);
    See Also:
    RemoveMatchedRecordsResponse, Serialized Form

    API Pair: RemoveMatchedRecordsResponse

    API Group: Data
